### Base URL Configuration
@host = http://localhost:8080/api

###
### POSTS ENDPOINTS
###

### 1. Get all posts
GET {{host}}/posts
Accept: application/json

### 2. Get a single post by ID
GET {{host}}/posts/1
Accept: application/json

### 3. Get pinned posts
GET {{host}}/posts/pinned
Accept: application/json

### 4. Search posts by keyword and category
# Categories: URGENT, INFO, EVENT, ANIMEGIRLS, HASKELL, BIGDECIMAL
GET {{host}}/posts/search?keyword=Java&category=INFO
Accept: application/json

### 5. Create a new post
POST {{host}}/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learning Spring Boot",
  "content": "Spring Boot makes it easy to create stand-alone, production-grade Spring-based Applications.",
  "category": "INFO",
  "author": "John Doe",
  "pinned": false,
  "createdAt": "2026-06-07T20:00:00"
}

### 6. Update an existing post
PUT {{host}}/posts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learning Spring Boot (Updated)",
  "content": "Updated content showing how easy it is to use Spring Boot.",
  "category": "URGENT",
  "author": "John Doe",
  "pinned": true,
  "createdAt": "2026-06-07T20:00:00"
}

### 7. Delete a post by ID
DELETE {{host}}/posts/1

###
### COMMENTS ENDPOINTS
###

### 8. Get comments for a specific post
GET {{host}}/comments/post/1
Accept: application/json

### 9. Create a new comment for a post
POST {{host}}/comments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Great post! Extremely helpful.",
  "author": "Jane Smith",
  "createdAt": "2026-06-07T20:05:00",
  "post": {
    "id": 1
  }
}

### 10. Delete a comment by ID
DELETE {{host}}/comments/1

###
### STATS ENDPOINTS
###

### 11. Get post count per author
GET {{host}}/stats/posts-per-author
Accept: application/json

### 12. Get post count per category
GET {{host}}/stats/posts-per-category
Accept: application/json
